IT Ticketing System Project – Freshdesk (2025)


This project simulates a real-world IT Helpdesk environment using Freshdesk.

It demonstrates hands-on troubleshooting, ticket documentation, and workflow handling used in IT Support and SOC/Helpdesk roles.

 Tools & Technologies Used
Freshdesk Ticketing System

Windows 10

Active Directory (simulated scenarios)

Microsoft 365

VPN Troubleshooting

Printer Troubleshooting

Network Troubleshooting

System Performance Optimization

 Project Structure
/screenshots – Full screenshots of every ticket, the dashboard, contacts, and company

/tickets – Written versions of ticket descriptions, steps, and resolutions

/documentation – Notes and troubleshooting workflows

 Completed Tickets (10 Total)
Password Reset / AD Lockout

VPN Failing to Authenticate

Printer Offline

Outlook Password Loop

Slow Computer / Performance Issue

Software Installation Request

Shared Folder Access Denied

Second Monitor Not Displaying

MFA Reset

Wi-Fi Connection Issue

 Skills Demonstrated
Troubleshooting hardware & software issues

Documenting steps and resolutions

Prioritizing tickets and managing workloads

Simulating real helpdesk workflows

User support and communication

Basic networking & account management

 Purpose of This Project


To demonstrate practical, hands-on service desk experience for IT Support or Cybersecurity entry-level roles.
